710066f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 13th Street (West)
710066f-b.text:
8th Avenue, north from W. 13th Street, showing the new County
Trust Company Building at the N. E. corner of W. 14th Street. At
the right is Greenwich Avenue and its cleared corner. Buildings
here were demolished for a work a)aft to the subway construction
underground. Later this will be leased for a parking lot. A white
ventilator building will be erected at the extreme right of same.
This structure is ot shown in View 2. The 2-story taxpa er on the
8th Avenue side has just been completed.
In the background appears the New York Telephone Build'og on
W7. 17th Street and the Emptre State Building (under construction in
view 1).
October 13, 1930
July 30, 1932
P. L. Sperr

710065f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 13th Street (West)
710065f-b.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from W. 13th (right) to Horatio
Streets as viewed westward from Jackson Square, showirg the base of
a triangular block that has W. 4th Street on its undisclosed side.
VView 2 is an oblique view southward from W. 13th Street.
No. 3 is detailed to show the new gas station at the 5. W.
corner of W. 13th Street. This replaced the structure there as
shown in the earlier view. Buildings on the rirht face on the
south side of W. 13th Street and extend from 8th Avenue to W. 4th
Street.
View 1: February 14, 1932
View 2: June 24, 1933
View 3: April 9, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

710068f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 13th Street
710068f-a.text:
(1)
Eighth Ave., east side, north from Horatio to 13th Streets. The
view also shows at the right Nos. 253-243 West 13th Street at the
intersection of Horatio and 13th Streets, east of Jackson Square.
Construction work is going on in Jackson Square in the foreground.
May 27, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, a year later, showing Jackson Square cleared, preparatory,
to making it into a miniature park.
July 30, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

710067f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 13th Street (West)
710067f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from W. 13th to 14th Streets as
photograohed from atop the apartment house, No. 2 Horatio Street.
At the right is 14th Street with its two bank buildings. Clearly
shown is the former New York County National Bank at the S. E.
corner. This institution was absorbed by the present Manufacturers
Trust Coapany. Partially seen is the New York Savings Bank at the
N. W. corner.
View 2 is the same locale, minus the aforementioned corner
structures.
March 16, 1933
February 14, 1933
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODICTIONS
